l in love with these Marry Me Chickpeas, a vegetarian twist on Marry Me Chicken! With a creamy Italian-style tomato sauce and nutritious chickpeas, this incredible 30 minute meal is perfect for date night.","datePublished":"2023-11-28T15:48:31+00:00","image":["https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-14.jpg","https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-14-500x500.jpg","https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-14-500x375.jpg","https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-14-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Marry Me Chickpeas (So Good You'll Want To Put A Ring On It)","description":"Win hearts and prepare to fall in love with these Marry Me Chickpeas, a vegetarian twist on Marry Me Chicken! With a creamy Italian-style tomato sauce and nutritious chickpeas, this incredible 15 minute meal is perfect for vegetarian date night.\n\nGrab the full written recipe here: https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/\n\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/liveeatlearn/\nTikTok: https://tiktok.com/@liveeatlearn/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/liveeatlearn/\nPinterest: https://www.pinterest.com/live_eat_learn","uploadDate":"2023-11-28T23:12:02+00:00","duration":"PT21S","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gL4OsJIbGJ8/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/gL4OsJIbGJ8?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gL4OsJIbGJ8","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"prepTime":"PT5M","cookTime":"PT10M","totalTime":"PT15M","recipeIngredient":["2 Tbsp unsalted butter (28 g)","4 cloves garlic (minced)","½ tsp each salt, oregano, crushed red pepper flakes","¼ tsp ground black pepper","½ cup sun-dried tomatoes (roughly chopped)","1 cup vegetable broth (236 mL)","2 15-oz cans chickpeas (drained, 425 g cans)","1 cup heavy cream (can sub half-and-half)","½ cup grated parmesan","2 Tbsp chopped fresh basil"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Flavor Base: Heat 2 Tbsp unsalted butter, 4 cloves garlic, ½ tsp each salt, oregano, crushed red pepper flakes, and ¼ tsp ground black pepper in a large saute pan or pot over medium heat. Cook for about 2 minutes, until garlic is fragrant.","name":"Flavor base","url":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#wprm-recipe-90865-step-0-0","image":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-1.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Fillings: Stir in ½ cup sun-dried tomatoes, 1 cup vegetable broth, and 2 15-oz cans chickpeas. Continue cooking on medium, uncovered, for 5 minutes.","name":"Add fillings","url":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#wprm-recipe-90865-step-0-1","image":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-2.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Finish: Remove from heat. Stir in 1 cup heavy cream ½ cup grated parmesan, and 2 Tbsp chopped fresh basil. Serve warm with crusty bread.","name":"Serve","url":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#wprm-recipe-90865-step-0-2","image":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-3.jpg"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.94","ratingCount":"192","reviewCount":"14"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolutely delicious and simple to prepare. Great recipe thanks!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sue Willis"},"datePublished":"2024-10-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"In love with this recipe… made it twice this month.. a def favorite","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jill Cunningham"},"datePublished":"2024-10-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Would give this recipe a 10 if I could!! This incredible soup will be a “go to” meal! Warm, filling and bursting with flavor!! A true masterpiece!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Oscar Hall"},"datePublished":"2024-10-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Delicious! I didn’t have sun dried tomatoes on hand, so used a half of a 15oz can of diced tomatoes. I also used my homemade vegetable broth that doesn’t contain salt. If you’re wanting to cut down on the sodium content in this recipe, rinse your beans very well and add a little water to whatever broth you’re using before adding it to the pot. I also added fresh spinach at the end, right before serving. Will definitely make this again!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Christy Lozano"},"datePublished":"2024-10-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"It was absolutely luscious! Couldn't stop eating it.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jane"},"datePublished":"2024-10-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"3"},"reviewBody":"I’m not sure what I could have done wrong because we followed the recipe exactly as written, but it was very soupy and had very little flavor. It also was pretty colorless compared to the pictures. It’s weird because I’ve made marry me chickpeas before and it was nothing like the version I made tonight.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"JT"},"datePublished":"2024-10-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I added about half a bag of frozen spinach at the chickpea step, otherwise followed recipe exactly - delicious!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sherry"},"datePublished":"2024-10-06"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Very flavorful! Next time I'll\r\nmake more of the sauce since it is so good.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kathi in NM"},"datePublished":"2024-09-29"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made Merry Me Chickpeas today\r\nDelicious.    Spooned over toast .\r\nWill be making again and again and again\r\n\r\nCliff","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cliff Ellerton"},"datePublished":"2024-09-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I made this for my vegetarian daughter, her boyfriend and myself. We all LOVED it. Going to be a regular to my cook ups.\r\n\r\nThanks for sharing. Shan Australia","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Shan"},"datePublished":"2024-09-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I Love this recipe! Comfort food, I have made several times. I substituted the cream with coconut milk and the cheese with vegan cheese and it tasted great.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kim"},"datePublished":"2024-09-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I added frozen diced onions and used half n half instead of heavy cream.  Roasted some broccoli to go with it.  So good, quick and easy!!  Will definitely make this again, thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dana Wilmoth"},"datePublished":"2024-09-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I’m so glad I found this recipe I’ve been wanting to use my garbanzo beans that I’ve had in my cabinet and I’m so glad I came across this recipe. I was so nervous to make this meal since it didn’t require a lot of ingredients but I also loved how it didn’t take very long to do and the flavor is very creamy and a little spice. My fiancé and I enjoyed eating this tonight I definitely will make this again. Thank you for sharing","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Karla Alyssa"},"datePublished":"2024-09-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This came out so yummy… I added a little more water because it started to dry up a bit. I also subbed the heavy cream w/plain almond milk and it still came out fantastic!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Latoya"},"datePublished":"2024-09-10"}],"recipeCategory":["Appetizers","Main Dishes","Side Dishes","Snacks"],"recipeCuisine":["American","Italian","Mediterranean"],"suitableForDiet":["https://schema.org/DiabeticDiet","https://schema.org/GlutenFreeDiet","https://schema.org/HalalDiet","https://schema.org/HinduDiet","https://schema.org/KosherDiet","https://schema.org/VegetarianDiet"],"keywords":"marry me beans, marry me chicken, marry me chickpeas, vegetarian marry me chicken","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 serving","calories":"432 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"44.2 g","proteinContent":"15.7 g","fatContent":"22.3 g","saturatedFatContent":"12.9 g","cholesterolContent":"66 mg","sodiumContent":"1204 mg","fiberContent":"8.3 g","sugarContent":"0.8 g"},"@id":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/"}]}</script>
