<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-storage">Storage</h2>


<p>This recipe <em>does</em> well stored in the fridge for up to 5 days (it&#8217;s great for <a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/vegetarian-meal-prep/">vegetarian meal prep</a>)! When ready to reheat, just pop it in the microwave in 30 second bursts until warm.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-protein-variations">Protein Variations</h2>


<p>Not a fan of chickpeas? Try one of these variations!</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>White Beans</strong> &#8211; add them at the same time that you would have added the chickpeas (see also <a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-butter-beans/">Marry Me Butter Beans</a>)</li>



<li><strong>Tofu</strong> &#8211; cube and crisp it up (<a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/crispy-air-fried-tofu/">air fried tofu</a> is my personal favorite)</li>



<li><strong>Soy Curls</strong> &#8211; this vegan ingredient has the texture of chicken and would be great here (<a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/how-to-cook-soy-curls/">how to cook soy curls here</a>)</li>
</ul>



